    <h2>SECTION A: Attempt any TWO questions.</h2><h3>Question 1</h3>
<div><p><p>What is a dual signature? Describe the dual signature operations? How is dual signature used during purchase request operation of SET protocol?</p</p></div><div><strong>Answer:</strong><br><style>body .mathjax_wrap{width: 100%;overflow-x: scroll;margin-bottom:10px;}</style><p><strong>Digital signature</strong> is unique, just like a handwritten one, because the private key is only in the possession of one individual. It is a close parallel to a handwritten signature. When used with a hash function, the digital signature is even more unique than a handwritten signature. To ensure the authenticity of the message, and to ensure nonrepudiation, the sender encrypts the entire block of cipher text one or more time using sender’s private key. This produces a digital signature that can be sent over the internet.</p>
<p>In<strong> operation of dual signature</strong> private and public keys are generated by the involved parties, who are the merchant and the client. Using their respective private keys, the buyer and seller digitally sign their portions of the transaction. A single dual signature is created by fusing the signatures of the client and the merchant. This composite signature is then used to confirm the transaction&#8217;s integrity and legitimacy. It can be explained in steps as:</p>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li><strong>Key Generation</strong>: A public key and a private key are created by the sender and the recipient.</li>
<li><strong>Signing</strong>: The sender uses their private key to sign the communication. By doing this, a digital signature is produced that can only be validated with the public key of the sender.</li>
<li><strong>Encryption</strong>: Using the recipient&#8217;s public key, the sender encrypts the message. This guarantees that the communication can only be decrypted by the recipient.</li>
<li><strong>Transmission</strong>: The recipient receives the encrypted and signed message.</li>
<li><strong>Verification</strong>: The communication is decrypted by the recipient using their private key. Next, the recipient uses the sender&#8217;s public key to confirm the digital signature.</li>
</ul>
<p>The Secure Electronic Transaction (SET) protocol uses dual signatures to ensure the authenticity and integrity of purchase requests. The customer&#8217;s bank uses a dual signature to both sign and encrypt the purchase request. This ensures that the purchase request hasn&#8217;t been altered and that the merchant can verify the customer&#8217;s identity.</p>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li>The dual signature guarantees that the Order Information (OI) and Payment Information (PI) are connected and unaltered.</li>
<li>It is used to authenticate and verify the identity of the merchant and customer.</li>
<li>It guarantees the confidentiality of the transaction information, as only the merchant and customer can decrypt the data.</li>
<li>The dual signature is used by the payment gateway to confirm the payment details.</li>
<li>It ensures that the transaction data is not altered during transmission.</li>
</ul>
</div>
<h3>Question 2</h3>
<div><p><p>What is digital marketing? Why is it essential in e-commerce? How do marketing metrics like click-through rate, bounce-back rate and conversion rate influence E-mail marketing?</p</p></div><div><strong>Answer:</strong><br><style>body .mathjax_wrap{width: 100%;overflow-x: scroll;margin-bottom:10px;}</style><p><strong>Digital marketing</strong> is the component of marketing that utilizes internet and online based digital technologies such as desktop computers, mobile phones, and other digital media and platforms to promote products and services. Digital marketing uses a range of strategies to reach customers, to convince customers to reach to products and services or convince them into making a purchase. Modern digital marketing comprises a broad system of channels including: Social media, Content marketing, Website marketing, SEO etc.</p>
<p>It is essential in e-commerce due to following reasons:</p>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li><strong>Understanding the Audience</strong>: Aids in comprehending and successfully establishing a connection with the target audience.</li>
<li><strong>Cost-Effective</strong>: Compared to conventional marketing techniques, it provides an affordable means of reaching a big audience.</li>
<li><strong>Reach Worldwide</strong>: Enables companies to advertise their goods and services to everyone, anywhere in the globe.</li>
<li><strong>Adaptability</strong>: Able to quickly adjust to shifting consumer preferences and market trends.</li>
<li><strong>Personalization</strong>: Gives companies the ability to tailor marketing messages to specific clients via social media, email, and search engines.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Click-through Rate (CTR)</strong> measures how many people click on the links in your email. For example, if you send an email to 100 people and 10 click on the product link, your CTR is 10%. A higher CTR means that the email content is engaging, and people are interested in checking out your products. This drives traffic to your website.</p>
<p><strong>Bounce-back Rate</strong> refers to how many emails couldn’t be delivered. For example, if 5 out of 100 emails didn’t reach their inboxes, the bounce rate is 5%. A low bounce rate indicates that your email list is clean and accurate. If the rate is high, it could mean you have invalid or spammy email addresses in your list. This helps ensure your messages are reaching potential customers and verifies that your recipients are legitimate.</p>
<p><strong>Conversion Rate</strong> is the percentage of email recipients who complete a desired action, such as making a purchase. If 100 people open your email and 5 buy your product, the conversion rate is 5%. This metric shows how effectively your email is driving sales. If the conversion rate is low, adjustments may be needed to make the email more compelling. A higher conversion rate indicates that your email marketing is successful in turning engagement into actual sales.</p>
</div>
<h3>Question 3</h3>
<div><p><p>What is B 2 B e-commerce? Discuss various B 2 B business models.</p</p></div><div><strong>Answer:</strong><br><style>body .mathjax_wrap{width: 100%;overflow-x: scroll;margin-bottom:10px;}</style><p><strong>Business-to-business e-commerce</strong> is the procedure for locating and accepting terms for the purchase of products or services. It facilitates the purchase of a business. One of the most important aspects of procurement is getting the proper amount, quality, pricing, and delivery time.</p>
<p>Various B 2 B business models are:</p>
<p>1.<strong> Network Market Places:</strong> Network market places are the online market places where different business vendors can gather and do transaction.</p>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li style="list-style-type: none;">
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li><strong>E-distributor:</strong> Companies that supply products and services directly to individual businesses are distributors. E-distributors are owned by one company seeking to serve many customers. With more products and services a company makes available on it&#8217;s site, the more attractive that site is to potential customers.</li>
<li><strong>E-Procurement:</strong> Procurement is the process of finding and agreeing to terms, and acquiring goods or services. It helps in buying to decide market value of the product or service being purchased by a company. Right price, timely delivery, right quality, right quantity, etc. are major components of procurement.</li>
<li><strong>Exchange market:</strong> An exchange market is an independent digital marketplace where hundreds of suppliers meet a smaller number of very large commercial purchasers. They focus on the exchange of direct inputs to production and short-term contracts or spot purchasing.</li>
<li><strong>Industry consortium:</strong> These are industry-owned vertical marketplaces that serve specific industries, such as the automobile, aerospace, chemical etc.</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p>2. <strong>Private Industrial Networks:</strong> A private industrial network is a digital network designed to coordinate the flow of communications among firms engaged in business together. The network is owned by a single large purchasing firm. It constitutes about 75% of all B2B expenditures. For instance, Walmart operates one of the largest private industrial networks in the world for its suppliers, who on a daily basis use Walmart&#8217;s network to monitor the sales of their goods, the status of shipments, and the actual inventory level of their goods.</p>
</div>
<h2>SECTION B: Attempt any EIGHT questions.</h2><h3>Question 4</h3>
<div><p><p>What does omni-channel mean in terms of e-commerce presence? Justify with an example</p</p></div><div><strong>Answer:</strong><br><style>body .mathjax_wrap{width: 100%;overflow-x: scroll;margin-bottom:10px;}</style><p><strong>Omnichannel e-commerce</strong> is a unified experience for customers across all digital devices and platforms. This strategy ensures that customers can interact with a brand seamlessly, whether they&#8217;re shopping on a website, through a mobile app, via social media, or in physical stores.</p>
<p><strong>For example :</strong><br />
A customer might start browsing for Goldstar shoes on the Daraz mobile app, then switch to the Goldstar website to explore more options, and finally visit a physical Goldstar store in Lagankhel to try them on.</p>
<p>With an omnichannel strategy, Goldstar can track the customer&#8217;s activity across these platforms, providing consistent product information, promotions, and recommendations, ensuring a smooth shopping experience at every touchpoint.</p>
<p>This approach helps Goldstar understand the customer journey better and create a more personalized experience, ultimately leading to higher customer engagement and more successful sales strategies.</p>
</div>
